1
00:00:05,131 --> 00:00:08,160
When you are genuinely 
enthusiastic about something,

2
00:00:08,067 --> 00:00:13,644
that’s the … And this is a little 
preaching thing here; everybody …

3
00:00:14,942 --> 00:00:18,056
is people go, “What or how 
should we preach, what should we do?”

4
00:00:18,056 --> 00:00:20,701
[Preaching | Share What You Like!]

5
00:00:20,701 --> 00:00:23,348
And I almost say 
the same thing all the time,

6
00:00:23,348 --> 00:00:28,185
although, yes—atma-jñana: we start 
with certain things about the soul,

7
00:00:28,185 --> 00:00:31,171
transmigration— 
that’s true, we do that.

8
00:00:31,181 --> 00:00:35,941
But, in addition to that, 
if you want to stay vital yourself,

9
00:00:36,653 --> 00:00:37,950
you tell people …

10
00:00:37,950 --> 00:00:43,507
‘Vital’ means ‘life’, ‘keep your vitality’, 
like in ‘not get bored and monoton …’

11
00:00:43,517 --> 00:00:47,404
“Oh, I said the same thing, 
over and over and over again …”

12
00:00:48,424 --> 00:00:53,963
If you will share what you’re 
appreciating, what you like …

13
00:00:54,361 --> 00:00:58,681
Just like when we eat something …
And this is funny too.

14
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:04,390
Like, mayavadis or impersonalists, 
they will say,

15
00:01:04,787 --> 00:01:09,707
“When you eat something 
very nice, you become silent.”

16
00:01:09,866 --> 00:01:14,296
You get it? 
That’s what they say.

17
00:01:15,441 --> 00:01:19,441
We don’t say that. 
And that’s not our experience.

18
00:01:19,446 --> 00:01:23,406
My experience is if you eat 
something very nice, you go like,

19
00:01:23,516 --> 00:01:24,666
“Wow!!!”

20
00:01:24,787 --> 00:01:29,987
You know, like, “Did you have this? 
Did you get the sabji yet?” or,

21
00:01:29,987 --> 00:01:33,653
“Did you get the sweet? 
You’ve got to try it!”

22
00:01:33,663 --> 00:01:38,113
Gurudev called Paramananda once, 
on the telephone.

23
00:01:38,113 --> 00:01:42,351
Paramananda is like, driving …
And it’s when Gurudev’s health 
is not good …

24
00:01:42,361 --> 00:01:45,611
And he gets a call from Gurudev, 
he’s going like, “What’s wrong?”

25
00:01:45,611 --> 00:01:48,131
And he goes, “You got 
to come back immediately!”

26
00:01:48,141 --> 00:01:49,791
And he’s going, 
“All right, I’m coming!”

27
00:01:49,791 --> 00:01:54,217
He thinks Gurudev is like, 
in trouble. Healthwise.

28
00:01:54,217 --> 00:01:56,587
And when he gets back,
he says,

29
00:01:56,601 --> 00:02:02,356
“Did you taste the sweet rice 
that Manasa Kṛṣṇa made?

30
00:02:02,356 --> 00:02:06,061
Did you taste this? 
This is unbelievable!”

31
00:02:06,061 --> 00:02:08,871
He called him, like, on the phone …

32
00:02:08,871 --> 00:02:11,161
He is racing back, like, you know,

33
00:02:11,161 --> 00:02:14,851
killed the couple of people 
on the way … But

34
00:02:14,851 --> 00:02:19,671
they, you know, they were 
run over in the service

35
00:02:19,671 --> 00:02:25,515
and got sukriti, 
they’re now in heaven …

36
00:02:25,515 --> 00:02:27,549
[Laughing]

37
00:02:33,519 --> 00:02:38,693
So when you taste something, 
anything, on any level,

38
00:02:38,693 --> 00:02:40,477
about Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

39
00:02:40,477 --> 00:02:43,493
that’s what you share with people …
They go, “What should I say first?

40
00:02:43,543 --> 00:02:45,233
Should I start talking …”, you know.

41
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:48,140
No, no—what you like.

42
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:54,711
When Bon Maharaj of Italy, 
Bhakti Madhur Bon,

43
00:02:54,921 --> 00:02:57,692
he came to the Math …

44
00:02:57,692 --> 00:03:00,835
He was actually 
a catholic priest previously;

45
00:03:00,835 --> 00:03:03,511
which is, like, an interesting story.

46
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:07,930
So, he comes to the Math 
and in his first meeting with Guru Maharāj

47
00:03:07,956 --> 00:03:12,216
he is telling like, “Oh, I’ve read 
some Bhagavad-gita …”, you know.

48
00:03:12,246 --> 00:03:16,281
And it was interesting seeing how Guru Maharāj 
is dealing with someone for the first time,

49
00:03:16,281 --> 00:03:18,801
and he goes, “Oh, you’ve read 
Bhagavad-gita …”

50
00:03:18,801 --> 00:03:22,081
He goes, “Which part did you like?”

51
00:03:22,081 --> 00:03:23,918
That’s what he said to him,

52
00:03:23,918 --> 00:03:26,785
“Which part of the book 
did you like?”

53
00:03:26,785 --> 00:03:31,163
And this is how he scored 
a lot of points quickly,

54
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:36,003
he said, you know, he is talking like-a ‘deeze’ [this], 
because have a little bit of Italian accent,

55
00:03:36,003 --> 00:03:38,753
and a little from 
a Dante place, you know …

56
00:03:38,776 --> 00:03:46,256
He says, “I like the part, where He says,
‘Surrender everything to Me, become My devotee.

57
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:53,966
Give up everything 
and become My devotee.’”

58
00:03:57,318 --> 00:04:00,678
And like, you could hear like 
a bell goes, “Ding!”, you know, like

59
00:04:00,678 --> 00:04:05,538
and Guru Maharaj is like, 
“Bless you, my child!”

60
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,930
So it’s like, in the eighteenth chapter, 
when Krishna says,

61
00:04:08,944 --> 00:04:13,834
“Give up everything and surrender to Me”, 
he goes, “I really like that part.”

62
00:04:13,872 --> 00:04:17,172
So Guru Maharaj is saying, 
“Hmm, interesting man.”

